[
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.1",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Canst thou draw out leviathan with an hook? or his tongue with a cord {which} thou lettest down? {leviathan: probably an extinct animal of some kind} {which...: Heb. which thou drownest?}",
    "hash": "7bbdb4fa8933da290cf18858cb3c64332249716f1b0dad57880fbfe983cd8149"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.2",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Canst thou put an hook into his nose? or bore his jaw through with a thorn?",
    "hash": "1a92527afcd25573d7b84d9bccb39941a9fd90b01adae9ff2bee0c99e6effb5d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.3",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Will he make many supplications unto thee? will he speak soft {words} unto thee?",
    "hash": "de5195327f9b3bcccc499eb6471577e9332028ef945e940733e40720e5ddff87"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.4",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Will he make a covenant with thee? wilt thou take him for a servant for ever?",
    "hash": "2e1aa60b890d481af53f29620747fa531dce18d6892be27d029458dc8830bd65"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.5",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Wilt thou play with him as {with} a bird? or wilt thou bind him for thy maidens?",
    "hash": "9ee504e115e0aef4ee8878103ec5bcc8c8c72c785882ad3c8f8caa3e823fc98f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.6",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Shall the companions make a banquet of him? shall they part him among the merchants?",
    "hash": "19ca6994ae5097ad37dd50a091c09b827ad5b8998f0420a381e8b19ed7e8322f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.7",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Canst thou fill his skin with barbed irons? or his head with fish spears?",
    "hash": "c3e54bfdf48aa7fe5a792b0c722075f5d85c1c38caaa52a78544ad1156a42e3d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Lay thine hand upon him, remember the battle, do no more.",
    "hash": "88aea0954a4cfd317e3e8ee0c62cecfc0a9f16fdba3fddbd55b70b24cdb86386"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Behold, the hope of him is in vain: shall not {one} be cast down even at the sight of him?",
    "hash": "b91303e204d5098607d32e874a03841038a1b66d9cc0ab10ece03d483f8e78c6"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "None {is so} fierce that dare stir him up: who then is able to stand before me?",
    "hash": "163a4a2302f5ad67b30bcf0ef65c9a878b79a239ac1a7bfc63c6380a8ff3ad5c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Who hath prevented me, that I should repay {him? whatsoever is} under the whole heaven is mine.",
    "hash": "89f29192572408218e6c00647457861b2456a061c97fcf496a137dcff65ef04a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "I will not conceal his parts, nor his power, nor his comely proportion.",
    "hash": "e3c7e6b33b215b5c78e996f0fa53b601af579e177fbeb9d621f7715aa165ebb7"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Who can discover the face of his garment? {or} who can come {to him} with his double bridle? {with: or, within}",
    "hash": "9ca40d3eee219b52064cf8e066e2f6a502ee0989c8f291101a69163ee312a28a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Who can open the doors of his face? his teeth {are} terrible round about.",
    "hash": "a7a0dbc6fa34b3da00f67519c260982365cf461905c7633044d793c176d5f268"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.15",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "{His} scales {are his} pride, shut up together {as with} a close seal. {scales: Heb. strong pieces of shields}",
    "hash": "4b09ce8a780fb9f26307556d6c2c8701e80564deef555ac431e233258b1a80cd"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.16",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "One is so near to another, that no air can come between them.",
    "hash": "693201ae1c45930cc20b47872e28acde286e50b04351f9c5d709436f71b69025"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.17",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "They are joined one to another, they stick together, that they cannot be sundered.",
    "hash": "b17146185312db13a27278d5d453ba827b1fb1bc1705b941002727397c8219b7"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.18",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "By his neesings a light doth shine, and his eyes {are} like the eyelids of the morning.",
    "hash": "6514f6e328c68c0fcc9a63177748fbfc402dc05047ca0d7ffa18a41f14dfda7d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.19",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Out of his mouth go burning lamps, {and} sparks of fire leap out.",
    "hash": "12e04c0f1bca25a1570879b9365ffb6bae08694ab628e8eaf42c87100c3f1116"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.20",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Out of his nostrils goeth smoke, as {out} of a seething pot or caldron.",
    "hash": "484c412c5ba5dedfb72057b9e7cfebc67a1468f876350f210281423640a7831c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.21",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "His breath kindleth coals, and a flame goeth out of his mouth.",
    "hash": "bc25842b65d346121f1e3e56ba0ad9eeaeca2437eb97cd3ead093eefc0d0c7cf"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.22",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "In his neck remaineth strength, and sorrow is turned into joy before him. {is turned into joy: Heb. rejoiceth}",
    "hash": "eb46b492f9cc2469bfc06394e0ba478cb6974f3aa37fe714dd6f15ea460efb15"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.23",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "The flakes of his flesh are joined together: they are firm in themselves; they cannot be moved. {flakes: Heb. fallings}",
    "hash": "e291350330b52b7b789f444cd66eb01e5c02c30badb6f215fbac2c334b96520d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.24",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "His heart is as firm as a stone; yea, as hard as a piece of the nether {millstone}.",
    "hash": "ade06bc50a2802e0b7f651d0a8c55989f80a983f31dc32f1e7b810e49588ad06"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.25",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "When he raiseth up himself, the mighty are afraid: by reason of breakings they purify themselves.",
    "hash": "7ba028c07ec48d3cbc4793ce135c1c90a504989dced09b81d8f44857c0705bac"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.26",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "The sword of him that layeth at him cannot hold: the spear, the dart, nor the habergeon. {habergeon: or, breastplate}",
    "hash": "72d2a827eb5b85d07e7841534f359fd1dd96f976372721510bcb8c4c8958d7a2"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.27",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "He esteemeth iron as straw, {and} brass as rotten wood.",
    "hash": "bed8c191c158f01dc8a1f339c37c43ce7d891d578b812502201cd19dc5b9aa23"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.28",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "The arrow cannot make him flee: slingstones are turned with him into stubble.",
    "hash": "b618fc77fa2730a8f17aa6a3cbd646b47c08834209546c46f9024f2fc25bb615"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.29",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "Darts are counted as stubble: he laugheth at the shaking of a spear.",
    "hash": "b9eacfc3d96703ffa33866a340125dbf57fcb891272ebddb5c8ccdf6344710b7"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.30",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "Sharp stones {are} under him: he spreadeth sharp pointed things upon the mire. {Sharp stones: Heb. Sharp pieces of potsherd}",
    "hash": "13806b84b3a5d66c474cab31eafeb446feca7035f8358ad40abf6c79d211b43d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.31",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "He maketh the deep to boil like a pot: he maketh the sea like a pot of ointment.",
    "hash": "27afdc0774a06c2b60132b743f69aeba0cca525f5b8a603c66d6741e2f257758"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.32",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "He maketh a path to shine after him; {one} would think the deep {to be} hoary.",
    "hash": "f192be3ba16a6f4125f83e2d7f3e6193bb56567a7a2ee9aaade05dfeb0038aff"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.33",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "Upon earth there is not his like, who is made without fear. {is made without fear: or, behave themselves without fear}",
    "hash": "d15b1014c431d785623ce013f9fc3d21c39433fce3a4d04580516e5c14305afb"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.41.34",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 41,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "He beholdeth all high {things}: he {is} a king over all the children of pride.",
    "hash": "871a1802cd300105c6a0cf419dd1063a039aee2379c7504934407a02f3a33194"
  }
]